    "course_title": "SUPPLY CHAIN CAPITAL MANAGEMENT",
    "description": "Supply chain capital management refers to the set of activities and solutions available to finance an organization's supply chain infrastructure.  As supply chains become more extended and complicated a need has developed to both manage and fund the supply network.  Define and study the various influencers on the supply chain capital structure.  Investigate risks, mitigation techniques, metrics and themes relating to the topic.",
